  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Building Surveyor",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Carrying out detailed building inspections and surveys to assess the condition and safety of structures</li>\n  <li>Performing building condition survey, leakage survey and defects survey on site to derive a good conclusion to the technical issue and make recommendations for repair.</li>\n  <li>Analysis defects and research data to support recommendation and findings.</li>\n  <li>Preparing comprehensive reports outlining any defects or areas of concern</li>\n  <li>Providing expert advice and guidance to clients on a range of repair methods</li>\n  <li>Proposal to resolve complex issues</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Degree in Construction Management/Engineering.</li>\n  <li>Degree or diploma in Building Surveying or a related field</li>\n  <li>Minimum 1 years of experience as a Building Surveyor in the construction industry</li>\n  <li>Strong technical knowledge of building materials, construction methods, and building regulations</li>\n  <li>Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills to identify and address complex building issues</li>\n  <li>Effective communication and report-writing abilities to convey technical information clearly</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team to deliver high-quality services</li>\n</ul>",
